content.text:
**Q2 — Renamed case:** `onboarding-conjure-srjcl` (parallels `onboarding-kludge-{nameplate}`).

**Q3 — Simple concrete suggestion:**

Each ordain case ordains exactly **one** vessel and propagates the resulting hallmark to a static list of consuming nameplates. No vessel is ever ordained twice in a fixture run.

| Case | Ordains | Propagates hallmark to |
|------|---------|------------------------|
| onboarding-ordain-conjure | rbev-sentry-deb-tether | moriah, srjcl, pluml (all GAR-sentry crucibles) |
| onboarding-ordain-airgap | rbev-bottle-ifrit-airgap | moriah |
| onboarding-ordain-bind | rbev-bottle-plantuml | pluml |
| onboarding-conjure-srjcl | rbev-bottle-anthropic-jupyter | srjcl |
| onboarding-ordain-graft | rbev-graft-demo | (none — graft-mode integrity check, no crucible consumes) |

This means `onboarding-ordain-conjure` retains a small new responsibility (propagating to moriah/srjcl/pluml instead of one specific nameplate), and `onboarding-conjure-srjcl` is exactly symmetric to ordain-airgap/bind — single vessel, single propagation list. Each ordain case auto-commits once at the end (clean-tree invariant for next ordain).

**Order with that simplification:**

| # | Case |
|---|------|
| 1 | onboarding-inscribe-reliquary |
| 2 | onboarding-enshrine-bases |
| 3 | onboarding-kludge-tadmor |
| 4 | onboarding-kludge-ccyolo |
| 5 | onboarding-ordain-conjure |
| 6 | onboarding-conjure-srjcl |
| 7 | onboarding-ordain-airgap |
| 8 | onboarding-ordain-bind |
| 9 | onboarding-ordain-graft |

(conjure-srjcl right after ordain-conjure since they're both conjure-mode and srjcl shares the GAR sentry; ordering is otherwise free.)

**Q4 — RCG-compliant named-string lists.** Sketch in `rbtdro_onboarding.rs`:

```rust
// ── Vessel directories ──────────────────────────────────────

const RBTDRO_VESSEL_SENTRY_TETHER:            &str = "rbev-vessels/rbev-sentry-deb-tether";
const RBTDRO_VESSEL_SENTRY_AIRGAP:            &str = "rbev-vessels/rbev-sentry-deb-airgap";
const RBTDRO_VESSEL_BOTTLE_IFRIT_AIRGAP:      &str = "rbev-vessels/rbev-bottle-ifrit-airgap";
const RBTDRO_VESSEL_BOTTLE_IFRIT_FORGE:       &str = "rbev-vessels/rbev-bottle-ifrit-forge";
const RBTDRO_VESSEL_BOTTLE_IFRIT_TETHER:      &str = "rbev-vessels/rbev-bottle-ifrit-tether";
const RBTDRO_VESSEL_BOTTLE_PLANTUML:          &str = "rbev-vessels/rbev-bottle-plantuml";
const RBTDRO_VESSEL_BOTTLE_ANTHROPIC_JUPYTER: &str = "rbev-vessels/rbev-bottle-anthropic-jupyter";
const RBTDRO_VESSEL_BOTTLE_CCYOLO:            &str = "rbev-vessels/rbev-bottle-ccyolo";
const RBTDRO_VESSEL_GRAFT_DEMO:               &str = "rbev-vessels/rbev-graft-demo";

// ── Nameplates ──────────────────────────────────────────────

const RBTDRO_NAMEPLATE_TADMOR:  &str = "tadmor";
const RBTDRO_NAMEPLATE_CCYOLO:  &str = "ccyolo";
const RBTDRO_NAMEPLATE_MORIAH:  &str = "moriah";
const RBTDRO_NAMEPLATE_SRJCL:   &str = "srjcl";
const RBTDRO_NAMEPLATE_PLUML:   &str = "pluml";

// ── Reliquary yoke targets (vessels that consume the stamp) ─

const RBTDRO_RELIQUARY_YOKE_TARGETS: &[&str] = &[
    RBTDRO_VESSEL_SENTRY_TETHER,
    RBTDRO_VESSEL_SENTRY_AIRGAP,
    RBTDRO_VESSEL_BOTTLE_IFRIT_AIRGAP,
    RBTDRO_VESSEL_BOTTLE_IFRIT_FORGE,
    RBTDRO_VESSEL_BOTTLE_PLANTUML,
    RBTDRO_VESSEL_BOTTLE_ANTHROPIC_JUPYTER,
    RBTDRO_VESSEL_GRAFT_DEMO,
];

// ── Hallmark propagation: per-vessel consuming nameplates ───

const RBTDRO_SENTRY_TETHER_CONSUMERS: &[&str] = &[
    RBTDRO_NAMEPLATE_MORIAH,
    RBTDRO_NAMEPLATE_SRJCL,
    RBTDRO_NAMEPLATE_PLUML,
];

const RBTDRO_BOTTLE_IFRIT_AIRGAP_CONSUMERS: &[&str] = &[ RBTDRO_NAMEPLATE_MORIAH ];
const RBTDRO_BOTTLE_PLANTUML_CONSUMERS:     &[&str] = &[ RBTDRO_NAMEPLATE_PLUML  ];
const RBTDRO_BOTTLE_JUPYTER_CONSUMERS:      &[&str] = &[ RBTDRO_NAMEPLATE_SRJCL  ];
const RBTDRO_GRAFT_DEMO_CONSUMERS:          &[&str] = &[];

// ── Kludge case targets (sentry+bottle pairs per nameplate) ─

const RBTDRO_KLUDGE_TADMOR_VESSELS: (&str, &str) =
    (RBTDRO_VESSEL_SENTRY_TETHER, RBTDRO_VESSEL_BOTTLE_IFRIT_TETHER);

const RBTDRO_KLUDGE_CCYOLO_VESSELS: (&str, &str) =
    (RBTDRO_VESSEL_SENTRY_TETHER, RBTDRO_VESSEL_BOTTLE_CCYOLO);

// ── Case names ──────────────────────────────────────────────

const RBTDRO_CASE_INSCRIBE_RELIQUARY: &str = "onboarding-inscribe-reliquary";
const RBTDRO_CASE_ENSHRINE_BASES:     &str = "onboarding-enshrine-bases";
const RBTDRO_CASE_KLUDGE_TADMOR:      &str = "onboarding-kludge-tadmor";
const RBTDRO_CASE_KLUDGE_CCYOLO:      &str = "onboarding-kludge-ccyolo";
const RBTDRO_CASE_ORDAIN_CONJURE:     &str = "onboarding-ordain-conjure";
const RBTDRO_CASE_CONJURE_SRJCL:      &str = "onboarding-conjure-srjcl";
const RBTDRO_CASE_ORDAIN_AIRGAP:      &str = "onboarding-ordain-airgap";
const RBTDRO_CASE_ORDAIN_BIND:        &str = "onboarding-ordain-bind";
const RBTDRO_CASE_ORDAIN_GRAFT:       &str = "onboarding-ordain-graft";
```

(Nameplate-string constants likely already exist somewhere — I'd reuse rather than duplicate; quick search before introducing.)

If you green-light this as the design, I'll draft the reslate and then implement. One last check: `onboarding-enshrine-bases` — what enshrinements should it perform up front? Currently ordain-airgap inline-enshrines the rust upstream base + the ifrit-airgap intermediate. Are those the only enshrinements, or are there others (e.g., for graft, plantuml)?
